altformavail.head: Existence and Location of Copies
altformavail.p: Some yearbooks may have circulating copies available at Mortensen Library. Digitized/digital copies of some yearbooks are available through MDID at: http://mdid3.hartford.edu/explore/explore/?c=allcollections:70.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The collection consists of yearbooks for the University of Hartford, as well as its schools and colleges. Some of the yearbooks in the collection belong to Hillyer College, Hartt College of Music, and the Hartford College for Women before they were part of the University of Hartford. The collection also includes one yearbook from University High School, a magnet school located on the University's campus.

arrangement.head: Arrangement
arrangement.p: The collection is arranged into six series by school in chronological order: I. Hillyer Junior College and Hillyer College, 1941-1957; II. Hartford College for Women, 1944-1998; III. Hartt College of Music, 1952-1957; IV. Ward School of Electronics, 1958-1963; V. University of Hartford, 1958-2019; and VI. University High School, 2008.

did.unittitle: Hillyer Junior College and Hillyer College

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series consists of copies of The Vanguard, the yearbook of Hillyer Junior College and Hillyer College, before Hillyer became part of the University of Hartford.

physdesc.physfacet: Duplicates, 2 hardcover (with brown paper wrapping), 1 hardcover (no wrapping), 3 softcover with red comb binding, 2 softcover with black comb binding.

did.physdesc: The reading room copy of the 1949 Vanguard includes pages three and four. All other copies of this yearbook have been found with this leaf removed. The scanned version of the yearbook includes these pages.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains copies of The Highlander, the yearbook of Hartford College for Women, both before and after it became part of the University of Hartford.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: The series contains copies of Allegro, the yearbook of the Hartt College of Music, before it became part of the University of Hartford.

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series contains the yearbooks and a few yearbook supplements of the University of Hartford's yearbook, from 1958-2019.

odd.head: General
odd.p: On page 166 of the 1967 Yearbook, Gail E. Fenn's photograph appears under the name Mary Jane Everett, and according to alumni from that class, Mary Jane Everett's image was labelled as Gail E. Fenn. The information pertaining to each student on the left side of the page was not switched and appears to be correct for each student.

physdesc.physfacet: Duplicates, One copy has graffiti on the cover

scopecontent.head: Scope and Contents
scopecontent.p: This series only contains copies of the 2008 University High School yearbook.
